data.text: Berlin's public transportation network makes traveling around the city convenient. The network includes the U-Bahn (underground), S-Bahn (above ground), trams, and buses. Fares are divided into zones. The U-Bahn and S-Bahn run frequently until late at night and on weekends. Berlin has two airports, Tegel and Schnefeld, which are connected to the city by bus or S-Bahn. When choosing a hostel, factors to consider include price, location, amenities, and distance from attractions. Some recommended hostels provide a range of accommodations and meals, and are centrally located.
